Consider the cube graph $Q_n$. We view it as the Cayley graph of $(\Z_2)^n$ with respect to $\{e_i: 1\leq i\leq n\}$. The characters of $(\Z_2)^n$ are $\chi_{I}(v)=(-1)^{\sum_{i\in I} v_i}$ for $I\subseteq \{1,\dots,n\}$. The adjacency eigenvalue corresponding to $\chi_I$ is
\begin{align*}
\sum_j \chi_{I}(e_j)=\sum_{j\in I} (-1)+\sum_{j\notin I} (1)=n-2|I|.
\end{align*}
So the adjacency eigenvalues of $Q_n$ are $\{n-2k: k=0,\dots,n\}$.

